         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1954"/><citedRange>733</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a7"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>248</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2 #b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1954"/><citedRange>714</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1995"/><citedRange>62</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3 #b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1990"/><citedRange>66</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1990"/><citedRange>66</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4 #b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">When you [pl.] come close to the Buddha, the teacher, sitting surrounded by a large crowd, then you [pl.] must try to see the thirty-(two marks) on his body.  (cf 83)</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:peyrot2013b"/><citedRange>254</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>206, 207</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1990"/><citedRange>38</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b7"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1990"/><citedRange>40</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="parallels"><ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a212"/> (completing), <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-yqii4"/>; MaitrHami 2, 4-5</note><note type="philcomment">This fragment, complemented by <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a212"/>, contains part of the second act of the Maitreyasamitināṭaka; it corresponds to <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-yqii3"/> b8 - <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-yqii4"/> b6. An Uy. parallel is MaitrHami II, 4a19-5a15. See also <bibl><title corresp="ref:pinault1999"/><citedRange>195-6</citedRange></bibl>.</note><note type="remarks">Due to the identification, verso and recto side can now be determined. It is the opposite of what is printed in <bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1921"/><citedRange>105</citedRange></bibl>.</note></p>
         </div>
